accountID.description: The account under which the processes ran.

atomID.description: The component ID of the Runtime on which the processes ran.

atomName.description: The name of the Runtime on which the runs occurred.

elapsedTime.description: The aggregate elapsed processing time, in milliseconds, of the runs that occurred.

elapsedVarSum.description: A composite value enabling computation of the standard deviation of elapsed run time for the processes that occurred using the [parallel algorithm](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algorithms_for_calculating_variance#Parallel_algorithm).

executionCount.description: The number of runs that occurred.

inboundDocCount.description: The aggregate number of processed inbound documents for the runs that occurred.

inboundDocSize.description: The aggregate size, in bytes, of the processed inbound documents for the runs that occurred.

launchElapsedTime.description: The aggregate elapsed wait time, in milliseconds, before the start of processing for the runs that occurred.

launcherID.description:
The API Service component that kicks off the run.
**Note:** The Runtime must have the **API Type** set to **Advanced** on the **Shared Web Server** tab of **Runtime Management** to specify launcherId.

maxElapsedTime.description: The time, in milliseconds, it took for the most time-consuming run that occurred.

outboundDocCount.description: The aggregate number of processed outbound documents for the runs that occurred.

outboundDocSize.description: The aggregate size, in bytes, of the processed outbound documents for the runs that occurred.

processID.description: The component ID of the processes that ran.

processName.description: The name of the process that was run.

reportKey.description:
The web service user that authenticated to make the run request.
**Note:** For Runtimes with an Authentication Type of External Provider, the reportKey is the API Key. Otherwise, it is the specified user name.

returnDocCount.description: The aggregate number of resulting documents for the runs that occurred.

returnDocSize.description: The aggregate size, in bytes, of resulting documents for the runs that occurred.

status.description: The status of the runs. Allowed values include COMPLETE, COMPLETE\_WARN, ERROR.

timeBlock.description: The start time of the represented time block.
